We’re running into an issue with our auto where after finishing a path the auto doesn’t continue to the next one. After running running our “Score J to human” the robot stops and doesn’t continue to the “Human to L.5” path. However when we run a sperate auto with just the “Human to L.5” that path runs. We tried adding a namedCommand after “Score J to human” and it ran but “Human to L.5” still didn’t run.

posts.name: Emre
posts.cooked: Are you sure score and intake command finished?
Yes, score times out after 0.5 seconds and intake is a runOnce command.
Also the auto runs fine in sim

posts.name: Emre
posts.cooked: Are you sure you didn’t exceed 15 second autonomous run time?
This shouldn’t matter right? Driverstation doesn’t automatically disable after 15 seconds unless using practice mode, which we are not.

posts.name: Emre
posts.cooked: Yes, Log command scheduler and run autonomous with just human to L5 path and make sure it can run separately
